<solution>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ol>
      <li><p>3:51 p.m. Sample responses:</p><ul>
<li>It’s 3 minutes to 3:30, 20 minutes to 3:50, and then 1 more minute to 3:51. </li>
<li>
<m>27 + 24 = 51</m>, so 24 minutes after 3:27 is 3:51.</li>
<li>If he waited 30 minutes, then it would be 3:57. Twenty-four is 6 less than 30, and 6 minutes before 3:57 is 3:51.</li>
</ul>
      </li>
      <li><p>4:09 p.m. Sample responses:</p><ul>
<li>It’s 10 minutes to 3:55, 5 minutes to 4:00, and then 9 minutes to 4:09. That’s a total of 24 minutes.</li>
<li>
<m>45 + 10 = 55</m> and <m>55+5=60</m>. That’s 4:00 and then it’s 9 more minutes, so the bus arrived at 4:09.</li>
<li><p>
</p><p>[@@@@@@@@] WARNING: Table present.</p>
